Java CLI Transaction Tracker

Description:
This project is a Command Line Interface (CLI) application built in Java that helps users manage
 and track their financial transactions such as deposits and payments.
 Users can add transactions, view their transaction history, generate reports,
 and search for transactions by vendor. All transactions are stored persistently in a CSV file.

Features:

Add Deposits: Log income or any kind of credit.
Make Payments: Log expenses or debits.
View Ledger: Display all transactions, deposits only, or payments only.
Reports: (Work in progress) Generate summaries such as month-to-date or year-to-date.
Search by Vendor: Find transactions by specifying a vendor.
CSV Storage: All transactions are stored in a transactions.csv file for future reference.

